Heat oil in large nonstick skillet on medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook 6 to 7 min. on each side or until done (170 degrees F). Add broccoli; cook 2 to 3 min. until crisp-tender, stirring occasionally. Transfer chicken and broccoli to plate; cover to keep warm. Add garlic to skillet; cook and stir 1 min. Add Cooking Creme, milk and zest; cook and stir 2 to 3 min. or until heated through. Plate chicken and broccoli with rice; spoon hot sauce over top.